UNITED STATES of America ex rel. YEE KWONG SEUNG, Next Friend of Yee Gwock Ming, Relator-Appellant, v. DIRECTOR OF IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION AT THE PORT OF NEW YORK, Respondent-Appellee. No. 283. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 27, 1939. James C. Thomas, of New York City, for relator-appellant. Gregory F. Noonan, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Myles J. Lane, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for respondent-appellee.

Before SWAN, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order, 25 F.Supp. 921, affirmed on the authority of United Stales ex rel. Ng Kee Wong v. Corsi, 2 Cir., 65 F.2d 564.
